@@ -0,0 +1,145 @@
+# PT Framework Connection and DI Documentation
+
+## Key Namespaces
+
+### Core Dependencies
+- **PT.Core.Model** - Contains `[InjectableImplementation]` attribute for DI registration
+- **PT.Core.Model.IoC** - Contains `IDependencyResolver` for resolving dependencies
+- **PT.Core.Model.Interface.Sites** - Contains `ISiteContextProvider` and `ISite` interfaces
+- **PT.Core.Sql.Connections** - Contains `ISimpleConnectionProvider` for database connections
+- **PT.Core.Sql.DataProvider** - Contains data provider implementations
+
+## Connection Management
+
+### Primary Connection Interface
+```csharp
+PT.Core.Sql.Connections.ISimpleConnectionProvider
+```
+
+### ISimpleConnectionProvider Methods (Found in actual usage)
+
+- `GetPtBridge(string siteId)` - Returns DataAccess for PTBridge database
+- `GetContent(string siteId)` - Returns DataAccess for Content database
+- `GetErp(string siteId)` - Returns DataAccess for ERP database
+- `GetPicture(string siteId)` - Returns DataAccess for Picture/Media database
+- `GetMedia(string siteId)` - Returns DataAccess for Media database
+- `GetLanguage(string siteId)` - Returns DataAccess for Language database
+
+### DataAccess Object Methods
+
+The returned DataAccess object provides:
+- `GetDataReader(string query, List<SqlParameter> parameters)` - Executes query, returns IDataReader
+- `GetDataSet(string query, string tableName)` - Executes query, returns DataSet
+- `LastError` - Contains error information if query fails
+
+### Usage Example (from SqlUsers.cs lines 126-136)
+```csharp
+using (var da = ConnectionProvider.GetPtBridge(SiteID))
+{
+    using (IDataReader reader = da.GetDataReader(query, queryBuilder.QueryParameterList))
+    {
+        while (reader.Read())
+        {
+            // Process row data
+        }
+    }
+}
+```
+
+### Usage Example for ERP Access (from SalemanRepository.vb line 172)
+```csharp
+using (var da = ConnectionProvider.GetErp(Site.SiteId))
+{
+    using (IDataReader reader = da.GetDataReader(sqlQuery, false))
+    {
+        // Process ERP data
+    }
+}
+```
+
+## Dependency Injection
+
+### Registration Attributes
+- `[InjectableImplementation]` - Marks a class for automatic DI registration
+- `[Injectable]` - Marks an interface as injectable
+- `[AutoBind(typeof(IInterface))]` - Additional binding configuration
+
+### IDependencyResolver Methods
+- `Get<T>()` - Resolves and returns instance of type T
+- `TryGet<T>()` - Tries to resolve, returns null if not found
+- `Get<T>(string name)` - Gets named implementation
+- `GetAll<T>()` - Gets all implementations of interface
+
+## Site Context
+
+### ISiteContextProvider
+Provides access to the current site context, which includes:
+- Site ID
+- ERP Type
+- Connection configuration
+
+### Getting Site Information
+```csharp
+ISiteContextProvider siteProvider = resolver.Get<ISiteContextProvider>();
+ISite currentSite = siteProvider.GetCurrentSite();
+int siteId = currentSite.Id;
+```
+
+## Referenced Assemblies in PartsTown
+
+From PartsTown.csproj:
+- PT.Core.Sql.dll (v4.18.0.3531)
+- PT.Core.SqlAnywhere.dll (v4.18.0.3531)
+- PT.Core.SqlServer.dll (v4.18.0.3531)
+- PT.Core.Model.dll (v4.18.0.3531)
+- PT.Core.Repository.Sql.dll (v4.18.0.3531)
+- PT.Erp.Repository.Core.Sql.dll (v4.18.0.3531)
+
+## Important Notes
+
+1. **Connection Provider**: The framework uses `ISimpleConnectionProvider` not `IConnectionStringProvider` (which doesn't exist)
+
+2. **Namespace Imports**: Always required:
+   - `using PT.Core.Model;` for attributes
+   - `using PT.Core.Model.IoC;` for DI
+   - `using PT.Core.Sql.Connections;` for connections
+   - `using PT.Core.Model.Interface.Sites;` for site context
+
+3. **DI Pattern**: Inject `IDependencyResolver` first, then use it to resolve other dependencies
+
+4. **Site Context**: Always available through `ISiteContextProvider.GetCurrentSite()`
+
+## Confirmed from Codebase Analysis
+
+1. **ISimpleConnectionProvider Methods**: Found! GetErp(), GetPtBridge(), GetContent(), etc.
+2. **Executing Raw SQL**: Yes! Use GetDataReader() or GetDataSet() on the DataAccess object
+3. **For weird ERP tables**: Use `ConnectionProvider.GetErp(siteId)` then execute any SQL you want
+
+## To Access Weird ERP Tables
+
+```csharp
+using PT.Core.Model;
+using PT.Core.Sql.Connections;
+using System.Data;
+using System.Data.SqlClient;
+
+[InjectableImplementation]
+public class WeirdErpTableRepository
+{
+    private readonly ISimpleConnectionProvider _connectionProvider;
+
+    public WeirdErpTableRepository(ISimpleConnectionProvider connectionProvider)
+    {
+        _connectionProvider = connectionProvider;
+    }
+
+    public DataSet GetWeirdTableData(string siteId)
+    {
+        using (var da = _connectionProvider.GetErp(siteId))
+        {
+            string sql = "SELECT * FROM weird_schema.weird_table";
+            return da.GetDataSet(sql, "WeirdData");
+        }
+    }
+}
+```
